Complex sed constructs are possible, allowing it to serve as a simple, but highly specialised, programming language. Flow of control, for example, can be managed by the use of a label (a colon followed by a string) and the branch instruction codice_26. An instruction codice_26 followed by a valid label name will move processing to the block following that label.
